imports.value: ensure, Get, IsType, Blake2_128Concat, Hooks, ValueQuery, StorageMap

defs.name: pallet
defs.docs:
The module that hosts all the
			[FRAME](https://substrate.dev/docs/en/knowledgebase/runtime/frame)
			types needed to add this pallet to a
			[runtime](https://substrate.dev/docs/en/knowledgebase/runtime/).

defs.name: Config
defs.docs: Configure the pallet by specifying the parameters and types on which it depends.

defs.name: Event
defs.value: type Event: From<Event<Self>> + IsType<<Self as frame_system::Config>::Event>;
defs.docs: Because this pallet emits events, it depends on the runtime's definition of an event.

defs.name: ClaimCreated
defs.docs: Event emitted when a proof has been claimed. [who, claim]

defs.name: ClaimRevoked
defs.docs: Event emitted when a claim is revoked by the owner. [who, claim]

defs.name: ClaimTransfer
defs.docs: Event emiited when a proof transfer to other acount

defs.name: Event
defs.value:
pub enum Event<T: Config> {
    ClaimCreated(T::AccountId, Vec<u8>),
    ClaimRevoked(T::AccountId, Vec<u8>),
    ClaimTransfer(T::AccountId, Vec<u8>),
    __Ignore(frame_support::sp_std::marker::PhantomData<T>,
             frame_support::Never),
}

defs.name: ProofAlreadyClaimed
defs.docs: The proof has already been claimed.

defs.name: NoSuchProof
defs.docs: The proof does not exist, so it cannot be revoked.

defs.name: NotProofOwner
defs.docs: The proof is claimed by another account, so caller can't revoke it.

defs.name: Error
defs.value:
pub enum Error<T> {
    __Ignore(frame_support::sp_std::marker::PhantomData<T>,
             frame_support::Never),
    ProofAlreadyClaimed,
    NoSuchProof,
    NotProofOwner,
    FailedToTransfer,
}

defs.name: Module
defs.docs: Type alias to `Pallet`, to be used by `construct_runtime`.

defs.name: Call
defs.value:
pub enum Call<T: Config> {
    __Ignore(frame_support::sp_std::marker::PhantomData<(T,)>,
             frame_support::Never),
    create_claim(Vec<u8>),
    revoke_claim(Vec<u8>),
    transfer_claim(Vec<u8>),
}
defs.docs: Contains one variant per dispatchable that can be called by an extrinsic.
